'''Merchas Ghazi Salih Doski''' ({{langx|ar|ميرخاس غازي صالح دوسكي}}; born 7 December 1999) is a professional Iraqi [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].<ref name="sw">{{Soccerway|merchas-doski/661035}}</ref>

==Club career==
Born in [[Hanover]] to [[Kurds in Iraq|Iraqi Kurdish]] parents,<ref>{{Cite news |last=Strašík |first=Lukáš |date= 5 June 2026 |title= Doski: S klukama z Plzně se hecujeme, že se potkáme v semifinále MS |url= https://sport.ceskatelevize.cz/clanek/fotbal/doski-s-klukama-z-plzne-se-hecujeme-ze-se-potkame-v-semifinale-ms-157217 |access-date= 7 June 2026 |work= [[ČT Sport]] |language= cs }}</ref>  Doski grew up in the district of Vahrenheide.<ref name="hage1">{{cite web |last1=Hage |first1=Christoph |title="Weiß, dass ich das schaffen werde": Merchas Doski wird Profi bei Wacker Innsbruck |url=https://www.sportbuzzer.de/artikel/merchas-doski-profi-wacker-innsbruck-oesterreich-celle-heessel-arminia-hannover/ |website=Sportbuzzer |access-date=16 September 2022 |language=de |date=19 July 2020}}</ref> He played youth football with [[SV Arminia Hannover|Arminia Hannover]] and [[1. FC Germania Egestorf/Langreder|Germania Egestorf/Langreder]].<ref name="hage1"/> Having established himself at [[Landesliga]] club Heeßeler SV he earned a move to MTV Eintracht Celle of the fifth-tier [[Oberliga (football)|Oberliga]].<ref name="hage1"/>

In July 2020, after trialling at the club, Doski signed with Austrian side [[FC Wacker Innsbruck (2002)|Wacker Innsbruck]].<ref name="hage1"/> He scored his first goal for the club's first team in November, in a 3–2 win against [[SV Horn]] in the [[2. Liga (Austria)|Austrian 2. Liga]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hage |first1=Christoph |title=Ex-Armine jubelt in Österreich: Merchas Doski trifft erstmals für Wacker Innsbruck (mit Video!) |url=https://www.sportbuzzer.de/artikel/ex-arminia-spieler-jubelt-in-oesterreich-merchas-doski-trifft-fuer-wacker/ |website=Sportbuzzer |access-date=16 September 2022 |language=de |date=5 November 2020}}</ref> He agreed a new contract until 2023 with Wacker Innsbruck in December.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hage |first1=Christoph |title="Habe hart dafür gearbeitet": Merchas Doski unterschreibt bis 2023 beim FC Wacker Innsbruck |url=https://www.sportbuzzer.de/artikel/merchas-doski-unterschreibt-bis-2023-beim-fc-wacker-innsbruck-vertrag/ |website=Sportbuzzer |access-date=16 September 2022 |language=de |date=14 December 2020}}</ref> His first-team game time was limited but he played in a friendly against [[Liverpool F.C|Liverpool]] in the summer of 2021.{{Citation needed|date=September 2022}} In May 2022 he terminated his contract at Wacker Innsbruck after the club had failed to pay the salaries of players.<ref>{{cite news |title=Weitere Spieler von Wacker Innsbruck lösten Verträge |url=https://www.derstandard.at/story/2000135374918/weitere-spieler-von-wacker-innsbruck-loesten-vertraege |access-date=16 September 2022 |work=Der Standard |date=2 May 2022 |language=de}}</ref>

After starring in the [[2022 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]] in Uzbekistan, he went on trial at [[1. FC Slovácko|Slovácko]] and later earned the move to the [[Czech Cup]] winners, where he established himself as a first team regular. He played with them in the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa Conference League|2022–23 UEFA Conference League]].

On 19 December 2024, Doski signed for [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcviktoria.cz/eng/clanek.asp?id=54431|title=First winter signing, Merchas Doski heads to Doosan Arena|language=en|author=Viktoria Plzen|date=19 December 2024|access-date=3 January 2025}}</ref> He played with them in the [[2025–26 UEFA Europa League]], reaching the knockout phase play-offs.

==International career==
Also eligible to represent Germany,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iretd.com/1377/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220330200108/https://iretd.com/1377/ |archive-date=2022-03-30 |title=ظهير مُميز آخر مِن أراضي المهجر يفتح قلبهُ لبلدهُ العراق مِن بوابة موقعنا تعرفوا عليه بالتقرير|date=29 December 2021 |publisher=iretd.com (Archived)}}</ref> Doski was invited to the [[Iraq national under-23 football team|Iraqi Olympic team]] camp in January 2022, and was one of five Iraqi players based abroad that were later selected for the 2022 Dubai Cup in March. He made his debut against [[Vietnam national under-23 football team|Vietnam]] and went on to play against [[Saudi Arabia national under-23 football team|Saudi Arabia]] and [[Thailand national under-23 football team|Thailand]] too.

He played in both warm-up matches against [[Iran national under-23 football team|Iran]] before being selected for the [[2022 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]] in Uzbekistan. He was one of the standing out players of Iraq during the tournament, scoring in the penalty shoot-out against [[Uzbekistan national under-23 football team|Uzbekistan]].

On 25 August 2022, Doski was called up for the first time to the [[Iraq national football team|first team]] to play in the [[2022 Jordan International Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kooora.com/كرة-قدم/أخبار/ميرخاس-دوسكي-يلتحق-ببعثة-العراق-في-عمان/1174586 |title=ميرخاس دوسكي يلتحق ببعثة العراق في عمان |publisher=Kooora |language=ar |date=21 September 2022 }}</ref>

In December 2023, Doski was named in the Iraqi squad for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] held in [[Qatar]].

In the Intercontinental Playoff Final in March 2026, Doski’s Iraq faced [[Bolivia]] and secured a 2–1 victory, qualifying for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] for the first time since [[1986 FIFA World Cup|1986]]

On 1 June 2026, Doski was named in the Iraqi squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] held in the [[United States|USA]], [[Canada]] and [[Mexico]]. Three days later, he scored his first goal for Iraq in a friendly match against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in preparation for the World Cup. Doski controlled the ball outside the Spanish area before scoring with a spectacular curved shot.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lowe |first=Sid |date=2026-06-04 |title=Doski stunner earns Iraq draw against understrength Spain in World Cup warm-up |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/jun/04/spain-iraq-friendly-international-match-report |access-date=2026-06-05 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> 

